During your use of our accounts, websites, mobile apps, or other products or services (hereinafter collectively referred to as the "HeyTap Product"), we may collect and use your personal information. Personal information refers to all information that is recorded electronically or otherwise and can be used alone or in combination with other information to identify a specific natural person.
This Privacy Notice explains why and how we collect your personal information, what personal information we collect from you, your rights to your personal information, and how we protect the security of your personal information.
This Privacy Notice defines general rules for all our HeyTap products. Given the great variety of our products and services, we also specifically develop privacy notices for some of our HeyTap products/services to explain in more detail how we collect and use your personal information during your use of those products or services. If a HeyTap product has its own privacy notice published, then the product-specific privacy notice shall prevail. For terms included in this Privacy Notice but not covered by the product-specific privacy notice, this Privacy Notice shall apply.
Before using the HeyTap Product, please carefully read this Privacy Notice to understand our practices regarding the protection of your personal information. If you do not agree to the terms of this Privacy Notice, you can exit the HeyTap Product by tapping "Exit" and we will not be able to provide you with related services. By tapping "Agree" and launching the HeyTap Product, you acknowledge that you fully understand the collection and use of personal information described below and your rights.
This Privacy Notice will help you understand:
1. How We Collect and Use Your Personal Information
2. How We Use Cookies and Similar Technologies
3. How We Retain Your Personal Information
4. How We Share, Transfer or Publicly Disclose Your Personal Information
5. How We Protect Your Personal Information
6. Your Rights to Your Personal Information
7. How We Process Children's Personal Information
8. Third-party Service Providers and Their Services
9. How Your Personal Information Is Transferred Globally
10. How This Privacy Notice Is Updated
1. How We Collect and Use Your Personal Information
We collect personal information in order to operate more efficiently and provide you with an optimal user experience. The personal information we collect includes:
(A) Information directly provided by you to us;
(B) Information about you obtained during your use of the HeyTap Product; and/or
(C) Personal information about you obtained from third parties.
The information we collect depends on the products you actually use, the environment in which you interact with us, and the choices you make, including your privacy settings and the products and features you use. Our products and functions include core service functions and value-added service functions.
When we collect information, you do not necessarily have to provide your personal information. For core service functions, if you choose not to provide the information, we may be unable to provide you with related services or respond to or deal with the problems you may encounter. For value-added service functions, you can choose whether or not to agree to our collection of your personal information. If you do not agree, you may not be able to use relevant value-added service functions. This, however, does not affect your use of our core service functions.
1.1 How We Collect and Use Your Personal Information
(A) We may need to collect your
phone number or email address, password, and sign-up SMS message
so that we can sign you up for a HeyTap Account and assist you in signing in to your account and using related services. If you do not provide such information, we will be unable to create an account for you or assist you in signing in to your account. After you have signed up for a HeyTap Account, you may choose whether to provide us with information such as your username, profile picture, and gender to complete your account details. We may need to contact you using the aforementioned information for survey or promotional purposes. Please note that you are allowed to sign up for a HeyTap Account with your own phone number. When you sign up with your own phone number, your device will automatically send an SMS message to us to verify your phone number, which may incur carrier costs.
(B) We need to obtain the list of apps already installed on your device to ensure that your HeyTap Account can successfully sign in to all the apps and services that support sign-in with HeyTap Accounts and to determine whether your HeyTap Account has signed in to these apps. You may sign in to your HeyTap Account to use the products or services provided by our platform. After you sign in to your HeyTap Account from your device to use the products and services provided by our platform such as HeyTap Cloud, App Market, Theme Store, Game Center, Browser, Quick Games, Global Search, Notifications, Soloop Cut, and Music, the auto sign-in feature will be turned on so that your user experience will not be interrupted, and these services will obtain your HeyTap Account information.
(C) You may sign in to the products and services provided by our affiliates or third parties that are accessible from your HeyTap Account, such as videos, wallets, communities, and readers.
(D) When you sign in to the HeyTap Product using your HeyTap Account, we need to collect your IP address, IMEI, OpenID, and Wi-Fi information. We collect this data to protect the security of your account.
(E) When you add a delivery address on the profile information or Rewards page, you may need to provide us with information about your contacts. We collect this information to help you quickly enter the receiver's name and phone number.
(F) We will collect and sync information on reward points and membership status of your HeyTap Account within the HeyTap Product and the products and services provided by our affiliates or third parties that are accessible via your HeyTap Account, and display it on the account information page to provide you with reward points and other member benefits.
(G) If applicable laws and regulations in your country require real-name authentication, we will also collect your
identity information such as your name and ID card number
. If you refuse to provide such information, we may not be able to provide you with the products or services you request.
